ided by the instructor whenever needed.)\nStudents are encouraged to bring a dictionary to class.", "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": "Students will independently evaluate the instructor and the course at the end of the semester. ", "備考Note0": "In principle, the use of smartphones, tablets, and other electronic devices in the classroom is forbidden. Students must store them in their bags throughout the entire duration of each class.  In the case of a project in which internet connection is necessary, the instructor may instruct students to use their electronic devices, but unless such a situation is specifically and clearly suggested by the instructor, their use will be strictly prohibited.", "更新日時/Date of Update1": "2025年02月25日 12時10分03秒"}, "campas": 0, "name": "【200】English Communication Advanced B　２／English Communication Advanced B", "管理部署": 2, "単位数": 1, "担当者": "プール　Ｊ．　Ｐ．（POOL JUSTIN PARKER） ", "履修基準年度": "２年", "履修登録方法": "申込制", "緊急授業形態": 0, "開講期": "", "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\n1. Active participation is extremely important and counts as a significant part of students’ evaluation marks. \n2. Attendance is crucial to students’ success in this course. The instructor will carefully mark students’ attendance as present and on time, late, or absent. Specific rules regarding attendance are as follows:\n2a) Only students who are present at the time the class begins will receive full attendance marks.\n2b) Any student walking into the classroom after the class has begun will be marked late. The instructor will take this into account when giving students a participation grade.\n2c) Being 15 to 29 minutes late will equal half an absence (0.5).\n2d) Each time students are late 30 minutes or more, they will be marked absent. However, they are still encouraged to attend. \n2e) As a general rule, no more than three absences will be permitted in this course."}